
This is a small programme that solve the skewb puzzle. The skewb puzzle is a Rubik's Cube like puzzle, which is equivalent to a 2x2 on a octahedron (i.e. it has 4 rotation planes). It is a relatively simple puzzle with few possible combinations (gods number here is 11 and the possible combinations are a bit over 3 million).

This programme brute forces the solution with not particular optimized search algotihm.

It also creates an image of the scramble.

Usage:
 gskewb scrabble [Options]

Scrable:
 Uses F, R, L, U notation
 Cube position: top white, left green
 White-Green-Red corner remains stationary (can only rotate)

Options:
 -s          Find fastest solution
 -i filename Output scrable into an image
 -h          Print this message

